<Author>gemmellian
<Content>OK but no A/C in the summer is hard Pros:- This hotel is very conveninently located to our Berlin site (within 5 mins walk) and makes for a very pleasant walk on the way to work - and back - everyday. - The breakfast buffet is excellent for the price (9 euros) and better if you could get it included in your room pricing. - Had dinner in the restaurant downstairs and the herrings were just superbly done (they are now in season). Say Hi! to Herr Schmidt - he will take great care of you as your waiting staff.- Super conveninent location of the Ubanh (subway) to anywhere else in Berlin and using a day pass if sightseeing (only 6 euros)- There is a mall right across from the hotel where you can purchase almost everything that you might need- There is a grocery shop next to the hotel where you can get snacks and drinks during your stayCons:- No A/C. I was there when it was over 30C and while there is a small portable fan in the room, it was clearly not enough. A revamp of the rooms with A/C unit would be most appreciated or even if there were some suites (I would pay the extra $$) with such amenities. - The snack vending machines in the hotel are rather lacking in variety so plan ahead and just go to the grocery store- No TV5 French Channel!! Almost everywhere else I go in Germany, I am able to catch my favourite French channel but not at this hotel- Wireless internet access is available through pay cards in installments of a number of hours. I found it rather expensive.- No easy access for ice cubes. I had to go fetch downstairs in the restaurant where they gave me a full bucket (yes, the one that you put the bottles in the ice) so not very convenient.- Room service menu is very limited. I tend to eat in the first night I arrive (jet-lagged and all)Due to its location and pricing, I will go back there but I just hope that it will be in the spring or fall and not the summer. 
